qas.question: What years dictate the Baroque period?
How have periods been reckoned Since 1900?
What era has the 21st century has been characterized by?

context: The major time divisions of classical music up to 1900 are the early music period, which includes <a0_0>Medieval<a0_0/> (500–1400) and Renaissance (1400–1600) eras, and the Common practice period, which includes the Baroque (<a1_0>1600–1750<a1_0/>), Classical (1750–1830) and <a4_0>Romantic<a4_0/> (1804–1910) eras. Since 1900, classical periods have been reckoned more <a2_0>by calendar century<a2_0/> than by particular stylistic movements that have become fragmented and difficult to define. The 20th century calendar period (1901–2000) includes most of the early modern musical era (1890–1930), the entire high modern (mid 20th-century), and the first 25 years of the contemporary or postmodern musical era (1975–current). The 21st century has so far been characterized by a continuation of <a3_0>the contemporary/postmodern musical era<a3_0/>.
